#Approach:

Rotate String – Concatenation Trick

Is problem me hume check karna hota hai ki goal string,
original string s ko left shift karke ban sakti hai ya nahi.

Agar s ko baar baar rotate karein,
to uski saari possible rotations s + s ke andar substring ke form me mil jaati hain.

Example:
s = "abcde"
s + s = "abcdeabcde"

Ab isme:
"bcdea", "cdeab", "deabc", "eabcd", "abcde"
sab possible rotations mil jaati hain.

Isliye approach:
Sabse pehle dono strings ki length check karo.
Agar length same nahi hai, to answer false hoga.

Phir ek nayi string banao:
check = s + s

Agar check ke andar goal present hai,
to iska matlab goal, s ki kisi rotation se ban sakti hai.
Otherwise false.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public boolean rotateString(String s, String goal) {
        if(s.length() != goal.length()) return false;
        String check = s + s;
        
        return check.contains(goal);
    }
}
